  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nThe basic logic for computing crosslink committees at a given slot was implemented in #148. As per the spec, a production implementation will want to avoid re-computing the committees for each slot. This implies we want to add some caching of the crosslink committee calculation to the `BeaconState`.\r\n\r\n## Present Behaviour\r\n\r\nEvery call computes the full committee assignment for a given epoch, even for slots in the same epoch.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\n\r\nThe obvious place to cache is to only compute the shuffling for an epoch once. Once the shuffling for the previous epoch has passed, it can be dropped from the cache. The cache maintains two shufflings (for the previous and current epoch) this way, moving as a two-epoch window focused on the current epoch (and trailing into previous).\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\nImplement the required caching.",
